content: Fingers warm-up now. The one who wins will be the first to answer some positional question, ok ? =)

Before going to the game I'd tell you some news about Renju Youth World Championship!
I got an e-mail from Ants just minutes ago from Armenia.

1. Okabe 10p from 11 (lost in last round to Nagao)
2. Timo 9
3. Johann 8
4. Vershinin 7,5
That was boys older group, aged 14-20
Later you'll see the whole standings.
For today's lesson I chose a game of my own again this time, too.
It is a game from last Team World Championship
My opponent was Pavel Makarov, Russia.
On 2nd table, like me. So we played.
Have you ever heard of him ?
Yes, he has played in the WC, A -final.
Yes, he played with Ando there, also.
6 dan in your age, not so bad :)
The time control was 2 hours per player.
I had to set the opening
The first moves are ordinary theory
You have seen it many times I guess :P
I didn't want to play k7
I thought I had more chances to win there.
K7 would be more draw maybe
Where is the correct move now ?
This is very popular variant these days
this is also the most popualr 14th now
In my last lesson we studied 14-j7 a bit
It was popular few years ago
and also 14-g10 is played sometimes. I have no clue whats the putcome there.
So, what do you think about this variant ?
black more active, but hard to win at last
Two main moves here are j7 and f7
Klimashin chose f7 ( I also played with him there).
lets take some quick look at the f7 before going on with j7
but how should black act now ?
White doesn't have win here, I think
so If we want to move j6, must play the four to f10 first
Ando and whte had similar game on REnjuclass 2nd online tournament
but does it lead to win ?
if black defends in a correct way ?
seems white doesn't have enough resources
i met it in the same problem,and my oppoent won me,:)
or what do you think Ando ?
i don't know, i play by feeling
and also if white fails winning in that corner
he might get some supporting lines or power to go on to lower side
so its an interesting game here
other 25th moves you must analyze yourself
white has other possible plans also
this was played against me by Klimashin
and seems now I made a huge mistake
and seems to be white is helpless
quite hard to say whats the outcome
what are the ides with this move ?
try to get activity from upper side
white had no time to play at i12 point
which are the possibilities for black now ?
i12 is more popular, I think
it forces white eo play i12 himself
at 鰁ast i12 seems most logical for white
better to close from upper side
then white has a nice way to win
or at least get very good position
can we play 23-L11,an try to VCT?
At left space,white seems strong,but nonthing
ok, no win here right, shaoping?
yep,but i think black win also,thx
there is no black vct after 22 on right side
that at right side no VCT
won't rush on attacking straight away here
That is how I had game against Kudomi
21st,then white get a stone 22st,so we need 21?
cutting black from going on left side
and these moves seem very logical also
I had to make a move at right side
because I didn't have VCF anymore
black had VCT on left side
so he could balance the left side a bit
now it seems pretty safe for black
I knew I would have troubles here with winning
needs a little luck and fight
but its also safe for white
and white doesn't need much resources to win in renju
tiny mistake can give me the win
I think there was some game also in e-mail WC
But I saw only moves till 31 I think
I think he didn't think about a win even for a second
its seen from his moves and also from variant
you answer with a killer too ? :)
so I must try to create some
but his answers are very good
so it is very hard to create something
that he will take h4 away
I thought it might confuse him
and its a good point also
now it's the e5 I said earlier :)
e7 - going on black right away, trying to defeat black!
c7 is then more stronger even
and I would waste my material
and the position would be way easier for black to defend
and there is nothing confusing about that move
and no power at lowe side
so, if black would play d4
31-41 would be long row and extra pair at 40-42
but I knew he would do that
I was ready to give away point c7 for lower space
but now black has a vct, do you see?
defend, also give power to lower side
18-42 gives extra strength to low side
the closest move to lower side
block and lower side is stronger
right now all my aim is at lower side
and 42 18 make a good inner support
and now there is something already
with precice moves I made something
black is quite in a trouble
its logic, 1 is defend right side with k5 another is defend left side with e4 for example
and the third is to try to defend them both with a very passive move- h5
this is very difficult place for white, I can imagine
You would like to defend both sides
and then u think about the passive one
black can make some fours and let the left side become narrow
fours give extra support for white actually now
I think in positional way of looking this
if there is little space but many lines
but simple line into wide space can be very dangouros
and it would let both sides open
white can have attack at right probably
but can try to get some support
so h5 is ogly and bad
I'm put into this little corner
can I win there or not
If I'll fail there I'll probably have no chance to win
so 45 was the best move from 'positional aspect'
it trapped me to the little corner, took away the space from my right side and also if black could play to right side first
soon there will be time problems
in real game you need to calculate all possibilities

here I thought i can win!
anybody wants to try to defend?
probably the only way to defend
black can't use his four anymore
but 53..55 eliminates white's possibility to go d8
and I couldn't see win anymore
I wanted to find a win still
He had also been very delicate with time :)
so he wouldn't be in timetrouble
cause he knew I would be much better in blitz
he somehow went on another world
I played 60 totally without any plans
but it must have confused him
he had possible to go b6 or b5
so there was blitz game possible
To play such kind of moves
this time it was a great timekiller
actually 60-a8 would have been more confusing and dangouros I guess
and now he had little time left
but a lot moves to mkae
as you see black moves quality is pretty low
and now I rushed into right side
I am not 100% sure it was like this :)
bevause we made the moves very quickly
and database has the game recorded wrongly also
I was like a blind kitten
I thought he can't play g11
but thanks to my stupid play
he was back in the game
we made the moves very quickly
great masters can win in 90th move :)
here every point is veryy needed
so its natural such things happen :)
Ando won Salnikov in a hard game
Ants won Artemiev on the 3rd table (ASV777)
and Timo had to accept a loss from Kozhin
so many people here, and yet so few answers to questions..
was the key of the game
